                            <comment id="15991794" author="zsxwing" created="Mon, 1 May 2017 23:35:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a reproducer: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/zsxwing/spark/commit/993b6d24d935cf489fdf643ef4266c239028d6e4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/zsxwing/spark/commit/993b6d24d935cf489fdf643ef4266c239028d6e4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15993426" author="zsxwing" created="Tue, 2 May 2017 18:09:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did some investigation using the reproducer. Looks like it&#8217;s not a class loader issue. It&#8217;s because the class initialization result will be cached. My current proposal is recreating a new class loader if a task fails.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
